<div class="docs-content">
  <span class="section-label">Getting Started</span>
  <h1 class="gradient-text">Quick Start</h1>
  <p class="lead">From zero to a running server in under 5 minutes.</p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <p>You need <a href="https://bun.sh">Bun</a> installed. That's the only dependency.</p>

<pre><code>curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash</code></pre>

  <h2>1. Create your project</h2>
  <p>Make a folder and initialize it:</p>

<pre><code>mkdir my-site && cd my-site
bun init -y
bun add index97</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Create the server entry point</h2>
  <p>Create <code>server.js</code>:</p>

<pre><code>import { createServer } from 'index97'

createServer({
  pagesDir: './pages',
  port: 3000,
  dev: true
})</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Create your first layout</h2>
  <p>Create <code>pages/_layout.html</code>:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
  &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;{{<span></span>slot:title || My Site}}&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;nav&gt;&lt;a href="/"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/nav&gt;
  &lt;main&gt;{{<span></span>content}}&lt;/main&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Create your home page</h2>
  <p>Create <code>pages/index.phtml</code>:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;template data-slot="title"&gt;Welcome — My Site&lt;/template&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Hello, world!&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Building websites like it's 1997.&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

  <h2>5. Run it</h2>

<pre><code>bun server.js</code></pre>

  <p>Open <a href="http://localhost:3000">http://localhost:3000</a>. Your page renders inside the layout automatically.</p>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Hot reload is on.</strong> With <code>dev: true</code>, any file change instantly updates the browser. CSS changes re-stamp without a full reload.
  </div>

  <h2>6. Add a handler</h2>
  <p>Pair a <code>.js</code> file with your <code>.phtml</code> to provide data. Create <code>pages/hello.js</code>:</p>

<pre><code>export async function GET(req) {
  const name = new URL(req.url).searchParams.get('name') ?? 'world'
  return { name }
}</code></pre>

  <p>And <code>pages/hello.phtml</code>:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;template data-slot="title"&gt;Hello — My Site&lt;/template&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;Hello, {{<span></span>name}}!&lt;/h1&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>Visit <code>/hello?name=Joey</code> — the handler fetches data, the template renders it.</p>

  <h2>7. Add a dynamic route</h2>
  <p>Create <code>pages/posts/[slug].js</code>:</p>

<pre><code>const posts = {
  'hello-world': { title: 'Hello World', body: 'My first post.' }
}

export async function GET(req) {
  const post = posts[req.params.slug]
  if (!post) return new Response('', { status: 404 })
  return { post }
}</code></pre>

  <p>And <code>pages/posts/[slug].phtml</code>:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;h1&gt;{{<span></span>post.title}}&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;{{<span></span>post.body}}&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>Visit <code>/posts/hello-world</code>. The <code>slug</code> parameter is available via <code>req.params.slug</code>.</p>

  <h2>8. Build a static site</h2>
  <p>For dynamic routes, export <code>staticPaths()</code> to tell the builder which URLs to generate:</p>

<pre><code>// posts/[slug].js
const posts = {
  'hello-world': { title: 'Hello World', body: 'My first post.' }
}

export async function GET(req) {
  const post = posts[req.params.slug]
  if (!post) return new Response('', { status: 404 })
  return { post }
}

export async function staticPaths() {
  return Object.keys(posts).map(slug => ({ slug }))
}</code></pre>

  <p>Then run the build:</p>

<pre><code>index97 build ./pages</code></pre>

  <p>Static assets from <code>public/</code> are copied automatically. Output goes to <code>dist/</code> by default:</p>

<pre><code>index97 build ./pages --out ./output</code></pre>

